adams.flow.control.Flow
	-annotation
	In this flow we are splitting a dataset into subsets, based on\nthe string value in a specified column. Using the iris UCI dataset,\nwe split on the \"last\" attribute, the class attribute, and will\nobtain three subsets, one for each class label.
	-actor
		adams.flow.source.FileSupplier
			-file
			${EXAMPLE_FLOWS}/data/iris.csv
	-actor
		adams.flow.transformer.SpreadSheetFileReader
			-reader
				adams.data.io.input.CsvSpreadSheetReader
					-spreadsheet-type
						adams.data.spreadsheet.SpreadSheet
	-actor
		adams.flow.transformer.SpreadSheetSubsetByValue
			-col
			last
	-actor
		adams.flow.control.Tee
			-name
			determine label
			-tee
				adams.flow.transformer.SpreadSheetGetCell
					-col
					last
			-tee
				adams.flow.transformer.SetVariable
					-var-name
					subset
	-actor
		adams.flow.sink.DisplayPanelManager
			-provider
				adams.flow.sink.SpreadSheetDisplay
			-entry-name-variable
			subset
	-flow-execution-listener
		adams.flow.execution.NullListener

